===Etymology===
From {{etyl|grc|en}} {{l|grc|ἄμβωνος}} (ambonos), genitive form of {{l|grc|ἄμβων}} (ambos) "rim, edge", and {{l|grc|κλαστός}} (klastos) "broken". Hence, literally, "one who wishes to tear down screens", in reference to the [[rood]] screens that separated the [[chancel]] (where priests were) from the [[nave]] (where the congregation was) in a medieval church.

